<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Signs and wonders are always linked to sharing the Gospel. It is never linked to some selfish request. All signs and wonders that are examples in the Bible are direct events that fully lead to none other than God being all-powerful.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Nearly every time that a miracle is performed in Acts, it is an act upon an unbeliever that becomes a turning point in their conversion to being a follower of Christ.</li></ul></body></html>